<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-10T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-10T05:00:00-05:00" n="621" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d621">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5431/192: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-10T11:00:00+01:00">June 10, 1935—11
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received June 12(<hi rend="italic">10?</hi>)—4:54 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>25. After Stucki’s visit has terminated I would appreciate it if you
                                would cable me a brief summary of what happened which I may have in
                                my possession before his arrival in Berne.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>